Deputy President David Mabusa is appearing before the National Assembly to answer oral questions. CAPE TOWN - Deputy president David Mabuza appears in the National Assembly to answer oral questions ranging from health, land to jobs. WATCH: David Mabuza replies to questions in Parliament  Mabuza says the belief that land under traditional leadership is owned by traditional leaders is incorrect. “This issue flows from the mistaken views that land under traditional leadership is owned by traditional leaders. It’s a false view. In terms of customs, it’s the people who own the land.” Mabuza's response follows former president Kgalema Motlanthe’s criticism of traditional leaders  who think they have a rightful claim to land. Motlanthe angered some by calling them “village tin-pot dictators” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)